Dear Mr. Vinny Prinu Vincent, 

As mentioned by others in the thread, some looseness may be expected in the rotor assembly or stator wedges. The lack of technical details on cooling air circulation, motor power, and lube system makes it challenging to pinpoint the exact cause of the high vibration. However, maintenance in the electrical power supply system and the mounting of the cooling air circulation fan impeller could be contributing factors. It would be helpful to know the relationship between the vibration readings in the horizontal and vertical planes, as well as whether the axial vibration is steady or fluctuating. Providing more information on these aspects could lead us to the root cause of the issue. 

Regards, Kris 

