            <p>Hello, last year, we encountered a similar issue with an 11kV Siemens motor exhibiting high vibration levels during testing. Despite multiple attempts at troubleshooting and seeking help from other workshops, the problem persisted until we decided to install the motor on-site. Surprisingly, the motor operated perfectly with acceptable vibration levels after running for two days. We tried balancing the rotor, cooling fan, and coupling separately, but we believe the difference was in the heavily cemented base compared to our iron base. The motor was tested with various bases, and adjustments were made to correct softfoot issues. However, the dominant vibration point remained at the center of the stator frame. If you have experienced similar issues or have suggestions for further testing, please share your insights. Thank you.</p>
